                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Much of the difference in perception is a gear thing.  If you're a bazaar-geared caster comparing yourself to a similarly geared melee, things probably don't look so bad.  So, it might not make sense to see things about the big disparity in melee/caster damage.  But, the difference in bazaar-geared and raid-geared casters in terms of damage, and most specifically sustained damage, is extremely minimal compared to the difference between bazaar and raid-geared melees.  
<br />

<br />
Beyond the level of gear where you can't max FT, the only gains in terms of sustained damage come from improved mana preservation and damage focus, both of which are very minor effects.  Access to spells also has a minor effect on sustained damage as the damage/mana ratio changes very little between spells.  Caster gear allows you to survive AEs, burst damage for longer, and better spells translates to higher burst damage.  In many situations, such as xp grinds or long duration named fights, none of that matters and the only factors of relevance are mana regeneration and the amount of damage generated per mana.
<br />

<br />
At some point on the gear spectrum, there is probably a decent balance between melee and casters.  At the high end, it tilts heavily to favour melee.  The only way to fix the problem is to either reduce the gains melees derive from gear or increase the gains casters derive from gear.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But, what else can a ROG do ? Very little other than DPS. 
<br />

<br />
What else can a Wizard do? or an Enchanter? or any casting class?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Wizards?  Well they can be a 5th rate snarer or get in the wayback machine to 2002 or so when ports actually mattered?  Rogues have similarly minor roles of stealth for recovery and picking locks.  Basically, they both do damage and thats pretty much it.  Whether mana considerations, resists, ae ramp, or ds invalidates or reduces that capability its still removing the only real purpose of the class.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
