                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
The penalty for going oom is you have to sit out of the fight for 5-6 ticks and then you are able to contribute again. If a melee runs out of hps, then they die. If a caster runs lom and stops attacking...without anyones help they can replenish their mana beyond buffs/gear and continue contributing. If a melee gets low on hps, they either sit there for 10 mins, or get another class to heal them. I see that as a greater penalty. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes, if a melee runs out of hp they die. But only when they run ALL the way out. Prior to that they can be healed for 7500 hitpoints at a cost of 400 mana.
<br />
This makes hitpoints relatively much less valuable than mana, which means a melee losing hitpoints to do damage is actually much LESS of a penalty than casters losing mana to do damage.
<br />

<br />
That being said, I still am not for it. 
<br />

<br />
