                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Guesstimating optimal setup:
<br />

<br />
Damage Base: 4070 damage
<br />
Crit : 4070 * 0.2 * 1.25 = 1017.5
<br />
Focus item: 4070 * 0.23 (45 % fire focus) = 936.1
<br />

<br />
Average damage/ancient core fire = 6023.6
<br />

<br />
Mana Base: 850 mana
<br />
Scm: 10%
<br />
Focus: 10% (Avariciousness of the Aneuk, 20% mana pres)
<br />
Evoc spec: 11%
<br />
Mana savings = ~31% (is this multiplicative, or additive?)
<br />
 
<br />
Average mana / ancient core fire = 586.5
<br />

<br />
Average damage / mana = 10.27
<br />

<br />
Mana Regen:
<br />
c6(20)
<br />
sa(10)
<br />
oak(9)
<br />
reyfin's(9)
<br />
ether(3)
<br />
ft(20)
<br />
base+med(25)
<br />
mana song from a bard in camp 100% of the time(22)
<br />
harvest (10?)
<br />
Maximum regen = 128 mana/tick
<br />

<br />
If we were to count e.g. an 11k mana pool in e.g. a 3 hour grind session it would translate to
<br />
11000 / 1800 ticks = 6.1 mana/tick
<br />

<br />
So neglecting resists (which as we all know are very significant) it would be
<br />
10.27 damage/mana * 134.1 mana/tick * 1 tick/ 6 seconds = 229.5 dps
<br />

<br />
With every regen buff, a bard in camp 100% of the time, and neglecting resists a wiz is less than half the sustained damage of a similarly geared rogue.  If you throw in xuzl pets, you might be able to get up to half.  If you consider resists and the fact that not everyone is going to have a bot enc, dru, bst, and a afkbard for manasong its quite easy to see how 150 dps would be a difficult number for a wiz to attain.
<br />

<br />
Another interesting note, if you compare wiz to enchanter, what changes in this picture?  In oow, scryer's about cancels out the extra regen from harvest, so the only things that change are the base damage and mana along with a very small amount from the greater number of crits wizzes get.  So, to compare enc and wiz sustained nuke damage its pretty close to just comparing their respective ratios.  For enchanters, this would be about equal to about the average of the ratios of psychosis and ancient neurosis as it would be very difficult to nuke out mana such that you didn't go fm (which means you are wasting damage) using only one nuke, so:
<br />

<br />
Wiz base damage/mana = 4070 / 850 = 4.79
<br />
Enc base damage/mana = Psychosis ratio (1513/375 = 4.03) + Ancient neurosis ratio (1633/398 = 4.10) / 2 = 4.07
<br />

<br />
So enchanter sustained nuke damage (assuming gear, specialization held equal) would be 85.0% of that of wiz.  Throw in another 1 or 2% more difference for crits probably.  Not only do wizards fail to do any significant amount of sustained damage compared to their melee pure damage counterparts, they also don't manage to do substantially more sustained damage than classes that were ostensibly designed for other purposes (although in the case of enchanters you can argue those purposes have been effectively removed from the game, at least for xp grinding).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
<br />
 Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
