I included harvest which i thought was about ft10.  If anyone has real numbers for harvest and whatever familiar that would be good to know.  I included mental clarity in 'base regen'.  The numbers came out right from what i know from experience.  When raid buffed with mana song i have 117 sitting regen which corresponds to the 128 minus 10 for harvest and -1 for having mmm instead of reyfin's.
<br />

<br />
I had thought scm3 was traditionally assumed to be 10%.  Also note that the assumption on mana preservation is _optimistic_ in that it is additive whereas its quite possible mana preservation is multiplicative (i.e. 0.89 * 0.9 * 0.9 = 27.9% reduction instead of 31% reduction).
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Something to keep in mind though. Most groups do not have a mob in camp all the time. Let's say your group spends 20 seconds pulling each mob and it takes a minute to kill it. Your wizard's effective DPS just went up by 25%, while the rogue's DPS remains the same... </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This is a function of competence,  gear, and the class composition of the group.  High % uptime is possible with just a good bard pulling, and considering the efficiency of CH and the hps well-geared tanks have now its pretty easy to maintain nearly full uptime just by dual tanking mobs.  Before, this would inefficiently tax healer mana, but at this point with a 16k or so tank such that you can safely land a full CH everytime, there's not much of a downside to tanking multiple mobs.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
