Again, I submit that no one has higher burst damage than a wizard, period, and burst damage is absolutely as useful as sustained</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I read parses all the time except for the retarded ones like 'hey look i did 1.1k dps!!!oneone' where it turns out they critted 3 times in their 40 second parse.  There have been some good ones on steelwarrior.  Wizards do still generally win burst damage but their margin is not that great.  It certainly isn't double what melees get.  Is it important?  Sure, on raids and in a few single group encounters.  For other single group encounters, such as many of the mpg trials, it has some bearing as the fights aren't all that terribly long.  For a competent grind group, burst dps is entirely irelevant.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648415" target="_blank" class="postlink">Londo Mollari</a>
