                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Several errors in this calculation. The most obvious is you take no account of resists (a real BIG issue). Also a 40% focus item means 20% average, its contrived to assume you will have a bard around for the 15% extra 'damage buffs'. Even 100 mana a tick regen is not easy to get in a less than optimal group. Taking all these into account you can see why they do about 150dps. Thats what I parse them at.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I skipped resists, true.
<br />

<br />
I did average damage adds.
<br />

<br />
12 (medding about half the time), 20 (FT 20), 3 (MC 3), 10 (Harvests), 3 (self-buff), 20 (C6), 9 (Po0), 8 (clicky)
<br />
---
<br />
85
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Edit: forgot 2 from familiar (or 10 if bard in group)</span>
<br />

<br />
Add in any of a necro (MW), SK (double-tap sucking), bard (21/tick, allows wizard to use mana-regen familiar) or BST (15/tick), and you are around 100 mana/tick.
<br />

<br />
Second, 95% uptime is simply insane.  Like really fucking insane.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Shinja wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">DPS is very misunderstood. Get a group of 3 wizards plus tank/heals/slows and get a group of 3 rogues with the same, the wizards group will run out of mobs to kill in a given area first, despite rogues having higher SUSTAINED dps. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes, but then the wizards will sit and wait for their mana to come back.
<br />

<br />
If your sustained DPS people are capable of sustaining that DPS with no more infrastructure than the Burst DPS people, the sustained DPS is superior.
<br />

<br />
Now, sustaining sustained DPS isn't trivial -- you need insane pulling abilities, and content that is 'easy' for your tanking/healing/etc -- but it is possible.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">At the very high end of the game you will find pretty much everyone puts out enough damage to clear a given area so fast its not even funny, so who really cares if someone does 'more in 10 seconds of fighting' when your having to pull from 4 miles away to find something to kill.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
